Injesting Baltimore City Data: Baltimore Religious Buildings

This project studies Baltimore City data provided by its local government on www.data.baltimorecity.gov. The purpose of this assignment is to learn how to import a chosen data set and plot its data. The data set I have chosen is the record of Baltimores religious buildings. Using R packages, ggplot2 and ggmap, I am able to plot the buildings on a map of Baltimore. The map is map in order to see the spread of all 513 buildings throughout the entire city.

source ("C:/Users/Tess/Downloads/Homework-2/RL.R")

Fig.1 Baltimore City Religious Buildings

This code chunk uses the properties of ggmap and ggplot2 to find the coordinates of Baltimore, create a coordinate map and plot the points on a map of Baltimore. There are 513 religious buildings in the city of Baltimore and on this graph.
